# Liquid Effect Animation

A full-screen fixed canvas background that renders a metallic liquid surface animation by dynamically loading the threejs-components CDN library. Supports loading an image onto the liquid plane with configurable metalness, roughness, and displacement.

## Use when
- Creating an immersive liquid metal background for a dark landing page.
- Showcasing a product with a premium, fluid cinematic hero.
- Establishing a luxury brand personality through an animated background.
- Adding a full-screen ambient animation behind above-fold content.

## Stack
- Framework: react
- Libraries: (none — loads threejs-components via CDN at runtime)

## Install
```bash
# No npm install required — library loaded from CDN at runtime
```

## Component — liquid-effect-animation.tsx
```tsx
"use client"

import { useEffect, useRef } from "react"

export function LiquidEffectAnimation() {
  const canvasRef = useRef<HTMLCanvasElement>(null)
  const appRef = useRef<any>(null)

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!canvasRef.current) return

    // Load the script dynamically
    const script = document.createElement("script")
    script.type = "module"
    script.textContent = `
      import LiquidBackground from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/threejs-components@0.0.22/build/backgrounds/liquid1.min.js';

      const canvas = document.getElementById('liquid-canvas');
      if (canvas) {
        const app = LiquidBackground(canvas);
        app.loadImage('https://hebbkx1anhila5yf.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/enhanced_8bfe61b0-d431-433a-8acb-49d508bf88b4-image-vWzKFKS7vQy7s8wfQYzEpaoiYaVMkr.png');
        app.liquidPlane.material.metalness = 0.75;
        app.liquidPlane.material.roughness = 0.25;
        app.liquidPlane.uniforms.displacementScale.value = 5;
        app.setRain(false);
        window.__liquidApp = app;
      }
    `
    document.body.appendChild(script)

    return () => {
      if (window.__liquidApp && window.__liquidApp.dispose) {
        window.__liquidApp.dispose()
      }
      document.body.removeChild(script)
    }
  }, [])

  return (
    <div
      className="fixed inset-0 m-0 w-full h-full touch-none overflow-hidden"
      style={{ fontFamily: '"Montserrat", serif' }}
    >
      <canvas ref={canvasRef} id="liquid-canvas" className="fixed inset-0 w-full h-full" />
    </div>
  )
}

declare global {
  interface Window {
    __liquidApp?: any
  }
}
```

## Demo
```tsx
import { LiquidEffectAnimation } from "@/components/ui/liquid-effect-animation";

export default function DemoOne() {
  return <LiquidEffectAnimation />;
}
```

## Notes
- Uses a CDN ES module (`threejs-components@0.0.22`) injected as a script tag at runtime — no npm install. Requires network access to `cdn.jsdelivr.net` at render time.
- The image URL is hardcoded in the component; replace with your own asset URL.
- Not suitable for environments with strict CSP policies that block inline scripts or external ES modules.
